summary: The Excel import parser was updated to normalize headers (including slashes, hyphens, and spaces) and to treat normalized variants like "karigar_factory_name" as a valid alias for the karigar/factory column, which should allow headers like "Karigar/Factory Name" to map to `karigarName`. No other requested UI/preview changes are evidenced in the provided diff, and the core row-mapping section is truncated so end-to-end behavior (e.g., defaulting to "Unassigned") cannot be fully verified from the excerpt.
